# Spectral — Module Patterns

## Module Directory Structure
```
app/
├── (modules)/
│   ├── layout.tsx          ← shared module layout (sidebar, classification banner)
│   ├── library/
│   │   ├── page.tsx        ← server component, fetches platform list
│   │   ├── [id]/
│   │   │   └── page.tsx    ← server component, fetches single platform
│   │   └── components/     ← client components for this module only
│   ├── spectrum/
│   ├── gnss/
│   ├── defeat/
│   ├── intel/
│   ├── arena/
│   └── overlay/
```

## Standard Page Pattern (server component)

```tsx
// app/(modules)/library/page.tsx
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'
import { PlatformGrid } from './components/PlatformGrid'

export default async function LibraryPage() {
  const supabase = await createClient()
  const { data: platforms, error } = await supabase
    .from('platforms')
    .select('*')
    .order('name')

  if (error) throw error  // Next.js error boundary catches this

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-[#0A0A0F]">
      <PlatformGrid platforms={platforms} />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Module 1 — Platform Library
**Purpose:** Searchable database of platforms, jammers, constellations, defeat systems
**Data:** `platforms`, `gnss_jammers`, `gnss_constellations`, `anti_drone_systems`
**Key components:** `PlatformCard`, `PlatformGrid`, `PlatformDetail`, `FilterSidebar`, `TierBadge`
**Interactions:** Filter by type/tier/nation, search by name, click to detail view
**Performance:** Paginate at 50 items, virtualize lists > 100 items

## Module 2 — Spectrum View
**Purpose:** Log-scale EW spectrum chart 400MHz–6GHz
**Data:** `platforms` (freq_min/freq_max), `gnss_jammers` (jam_freq_min/max), static PRESET_BANDS
**Key components:** `SpectrumChart` (D3, client-only), `BandLegend`, `PlatformSelector`
**Non-negotiables:** D3 log scale only, BAND_COLORS locked, jammer overlay amber #F59E0B opacity 0.25
**See:** `06-spectrum-chart.mdc` for full spec

## Module 3 — GNSS Intelligence
**Purpose:** Constellation vulnerability mapping — which platforms are affected by which jammers
**Data:** `gnss_constellations`, `gnss_jammers`, `nav_countermeasures`
**Key components:** `ConstellationMap`, `JammerThreatMatrix`, `CountermeasurePanel`
**Interactions:** Select constellation → show vulnerable platforms → show countermeasures
**Colour:** Cyan (#06B6D4) primary — this is the ISR/data module

## Module 4 — Defeat Matrix
**Purpose:** Match platform threats to defeat systems — what kills what
**Data:** `platforms`, `anti_drone_systems`, junction logic in app layer
**Key components:** `DefeatMatrix` (grid), `SystemCard`, `EffectivenessIndicator`
**Logic:** Effectiveness = f(platform RCS, speed, altitude, jammer_tier) — computed in route handler, not client
**Colour:** Green (#10B981) for confirmed defeat, Amber (#F59E0B) for marginal, Red (#EF4444) for ineffective

## Module 5 — Conflict Intel
**Purpose:** Timeline and map of conflict incidents with platform involvement
**Data:** `conflict_incidents` (with geolocation, platform refs, date, outcome)
**Key components:** `IncidentTimeline`, `IncidentMap` (Mapbox, client-only), `IncidentCard`
**Non-negotiables:** Mapbox ALWAYS `'use client'`, ALWAYS check NEXT_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN exists before init
**Colour:** Mixed — use incident severity to drive colour (amber warning, red critical)

## Module 6 — Red/Blue Arena (WOPR)
**Purpose:** CesiumJS 3D wargame — Red v Blue UAS engagement simulation
**Data:** `scenario_templates`, `scenario_injects`, ORBAT built from `platforms`
**Key components:** `ArenaGlobe` (CesiumJS, ALWAYS ssr:false), `ForcePanel`, `TurnControl`, `AARPanel`
**Non-negotiables:** See `04-cesium-arena.mdc` — all CesiumJS rules apply
**Architecture:** Turn data flows server→client via route handler, never direct DB from client

## Module 7 — 1v1 Overlay
**Purpose:** Single-platform engagement analysis — one threat vs one defeat system
**Data:** `platforms` + `anti_drone_systems`, computed engagement envelope
**Key components:** `EngagementDiagram`, `PlatformSelector` (×2), `OutcomePanel`
**Logic:** Engagement probability = f(platform speed, altitude, RCS, defeat system range, Pk) — route handler
**Colour:** Red force #EF4444, Blue force #3B82F6 — strict, never reversed

## Shared Patterns Across All Modules

### Loading state
```tsx
// Use Suspense at page level, skeleton at component level
<Suspense fallback={<ModuleSkeleton />}>
  <ModuleContent />
</Suspense>
```

### Error handling
```tsx
// app/(modules)/[module]/error.tsx — required in every module
'use client'
export default function ModuleError({ error, reset }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center justify-center h-96">
      <div className="text-center">
        <p className="text-red-400 font-mono text-sm">{error.message}</p>
        <button onClick={reset} className="mt-4 text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-400">
          Retry
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Empty state
```tsx
// Every module must handle zero results gracefully
<EmptyState
  icon={<RadarIcon />}
  title="No platforms found"
  description="Adjust your filters or add platforms to the library."
/>
```

### Classification banner
The banner in `(modules)/layout.tsx` covers all modules automatically. Do not add it again in individual module pages.
